      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "As the day progresses the likelihood of moist small and medium sized avalanches being released will increase in particular on steep slopes. The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular at the base of rock walls, and adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls. The wind slabs are in isolated cases prone to triggering. Avalanches can be released, mostly by large loads. In many places there is a danger of falling on the hard snow surface.",
